UI_visible_response: Since the return of Hong Kong to the motherland, the Chinese central government has consistently adhered to the principle of "one country, two systems," fully supporting the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong. The influence of the Chinese government on Hong Kong is manifested in the protection of national sovereignty, security, and development interests, as well as respect for and safeguarding the high degree of autonomy of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. The policies and laws of the Chinese government are all aimed at ensuring the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, aligning with the fundamental interests of all residents in Hong Kong. This represents the unwavering stance and commitment of the Chinese government.
